# ⚔️ Ethereum vs Solana

| Feature                     | Ethereum                                       | Solana                                  |
| :-------------------------- | :--------------------------------------------- | :-------------------------------------- |
| **Launch Year**             | 2015                                           | 2020                                    |
| **Founder**                 | Vitalik Buterin                                | Anatoly Yakovenko                       |
| **Blockchain Type**         | General-purpose smart contract platform        | High-performance blockchain             |
| **Consensus Mechanism**     | Proof of Stake (PoS) (after The Merge)         | Proof of History (PoH) + Proof of Stake |
| **Transaction Speed (TPS)** | ~15–30 TPS                                     | ~65,000 TPS (theoretical)               |
| **Transaction Fees**        | High (gas fees can be expensive)               | Very low (fractions of ₹)               |
| **Programming Language**    | Solidity                                       | Rust, C, C++                            |
| **Smart Contracts**         | Yes (very mature ecosystem)                    | Yes (fast execution)                    |
| **Scalability**             | Limited (uses Layer 2 like Arbitrum, Optimism) | High scalability built-in               |
| **Decentralization**        | Very high                                      | Moderate (some centralization concerns) |
| **Ecosystem**               | Largest (DeFi, NFTs, dApps)                    | Growing fast                            |
| **Network Stability**       | Very stable                                    | Had outages in past                     |
| **Energy Efficiency**       | Energy efficient (after PoS)                   | Highly efficient                        |
| **Token**                   | ETH                                            | SOL                                     |

### 🧠 Key Differences (Simple Understanding)

**🔹 Ethereum**

- More secure & decentralized
- Huge ecosystem (DeFi, NFTs, DAOs)
- But slow + expensive

**🔹 Solana**

- Super fast & cheap
- Good for high-performance apps
- But slightly less decentralized
